Text: Tangerine: Notice the "816p". That means that the vertical resolution (from the bottom of the video to the top) is 816 pixels high. On a normal 700MB DVDRip the vertical resolution is usually around 300 pixels. Which means that this HD version is more than 4 times the resolution (video pixel count) of those.
